tableflip
-----------
A simple (lol, no) program to format tables like that:

                            [file: example/pls]
| Language name           | 1st run | 5th run |
|-------------------------|---------|---------|
| Python (default)        | 82.322  | 83.084  |
| Ruby                    | 54.587  | 55.199  |
| C# (.NET 5)             | 4.845   | 4.689   |
| Python (numba)          | 300.802 | 3.172   |
| JavaScript (node.js 16) | 5       | 1       |
| C (gcc)                 | 2.757   | 2.816   |
| Crystal                 | 1.259   | 1.018   |
| Rust                    | 0.944   | 1.010   |
| C (clang)               | 0.744   | 0.735   |

1. Usage
--------

Generate a table from file:
+------------------+
| tableflip <file> |
+------------------+

2. Tables syntax
----------------
First line are header.
Line example:
+----------------------------------+
| "First column" "2nd..." "3rd..." |
+----------------------------------+

Note: max columns count depends on columns count
  in first row (header).
If header row contains 3 columns, but Nth row contains
  2 (or less) columns, missing colums will be considered
  empty.

